        public ProteinSequence translate(NucleotideSequence sequence,
                                 Frame frame)
        Description copied from interface: TranslationTable
        Translate the given ungapped NucleotideSequence into an ProteinSequence using the given Frame. If the sequence in the given frame is not a multiple of 3, then this method will translate as many bases as possible, any "left over" bases will not be translated.
        Specified by:
        translate in interface TranslationTable
        Parameters:
        sequence - the sequence to translate; can not be null and can not contain gaps.
        frame - the Frame to use; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new ProteinSequence, will never be null, but may be empty if the sequence is empty or less than 3 bp after frame is taken into account.

      • translate

        public ProteinSequence translate(NucleotideSequence sequence,
                                 Frame frame,
                                 int length,
                                 boolean substituteStart)
        Description copied from interface: TranslationTable
        Translate the given ungapped NucleotideSequence into an ProteinSequence using the given Frame. If the sequence in the given frame is not a multiple of 3, then this method will translate as many bases as possible, any "left over" bases will not be translated.
        Specified by:
        translate in interface TranslationTable
        Parameters:
        sequence - the sequence to translate; can not be null and can not contain gaps.
        frame - the Frame to use; can not be null.
        length - the number of elements in the given sequence.
        substituteStart - should the start codons be substituted with the translated amino acid.
        Returns:
        a new ProteinSequence, will never be null, but may be empty if the sequence is empty or less than 3 bp after frame is taken into account.
